9:
Mary! Sorry, looks like I kept you
waiting.
12:
Not at all! I just showed up a little
early.
16:
This is Mary, the girl I was just talking
about. She works at a confectionery
and helped me pick out chocolates
when I was there.
19:
We got along right away since she
was super nice right off the bat. So I
asked her about helping out today,
and she agreed!
23:
That's right! Now, I heard that
someone wants to learn how to
make chocolates...
29:
I'm Stella, nice to meet you. I'll do my
best to learn.
33:
Sounds great, Stella! Nice to meet
you, too!
39:
Um... I came here because I was
worried, but are you sure this is
going to work out? Seriously, this
girl's as clumsy as they come...
44:
Don't worry, I came prepared! We'll
be following a super-simple recipe
today, so we can't go wrong!
57:
It's... It's okay, Stella! Fifty attempts
down the line and I'm starting to be
able to make out the shape you're
going for!
60:
You have the desire to try, don't you?
That means you're not hopeless!
62:
Let's try again, okay? I'll stay with you
for as long as it takes.
70:
After all, you're doing this so that
you can confess your feelings to
someone, right? That's why I'll do
whatever I can to help!
79:
Oh, uh... Yeah, you've got it all wrong.
Stella just wants to give out
chocolates to friends, you know?
84:
O-oh! Uh... Either way, I want to help
her, though!
87:
Sorry, I completely misunderstood
the situation. My mind was already
focused on that kind of scenario, or
something!
107:
Mary, my dearest friend. Tell me
everything.
142:
Never mind that now, just show me
your hand! It's all scratched up...
147:
So... Can I help you with those sheep
that ran off? Maybe I could—
152:
N-n-no, it's okay! Really! I've got a
bunch of those adventurers helping
me already, so, it, uh... It'll be fine!
155:
So you can, uh... Let go of my
h-hand...
160:
O-oh! I wasn't trying to... I just... I
c-can't heal without physical
contact!
163:
Y-you've gotta go now, right? Don't
push yourself too hard!
173:
Ahaha...ha... Didn't expect to bump
into an acquaintance out here.
Anyway, let's get back to work—
176:
I've seen this scenario play out in a
million comics by now. Just get to
kissing each other already.
180: I've seen it in operas as well.
185:
H-huh?! I d-don't know what you're
talking about, but you're wrong—
201:
Not YET, huh? Perhaps it's still a little
early.
207:
Right! The timing's important, after
all!
211:
I don't know though, did you see
them just now? If she bumped into
him in the hallway, I'm sure she
could—
215:
It's not just about finding the right
opportunity, Nate. You have to be
mentally ready as well!
219:
Y-yeah! Even if I find an opportunity
to tell him, I just—
223:
Have you had a chance to tell him
already?
227:
Better question. How MANY chances
have you had?
231:
...I probably have a chance every
time we meet...
240:
I'm trying, okay?! I really am! I just
can't put the words together!
248:
You're helping me, so I want to help
you too.
259:
You have the guarantee of House
Felder... No, we make this promise to
you as your friends! We will do
everything we can to help you with
your confession!
272:
But, uh... Stella is... Well, Stella...
Reticia's love life hasn't gone
anywhere, and I don't have any
experience to speak of, either...
276:
...Ah, whatever. It'll work out
somehow, right? Yeah it will!
